    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A carbon ink made from burning tung oil with a low oxygen component. Originally in the form of a solid, imported to Europe as compressed sticks. Also, fluid consisting of the pigment suspended in a medium such as water combined with a glutinous binder.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
